              id: 1,
              name: "Cyberdelia",
              sidebar:
                "# Cyberdelia\n\nCyberdelia is a small and humble oasis in the middle of cyberspace. We navigate cyberspace with our small fleet of nodes, geographically distributed yet cohesively united through the cyberspace, dredging the dangerous digital waters of self-hosting, fighting face-to-face with the kraken that comes with poweroutages, facing dangerous storms of ISP outages and persisting against the inclement gusts of disk failures that \nknock the wind out of our sails.\n\nThis instance of [Lemmy](https://join-lemmy.org/), is part of Cyberdelia, a decentralized network with mixed resources and infrastructure, self-hosted domestically and rarely using VPS.\n\n*It is possible that some of the services linked here may be down*.\n\nWe believe that privacy is very important and that technological sovereignty begins at home, therefore, we give vital importance to the self-hosting of decentralized and interoperable services by individuals and communities.\n\nTrust your technolust!",
